hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Dispersion (Kane model): 
$$\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)=\frac{\hbar^2k^2}{2m_0}.$$
2. Group velocity: differentiate w.r.t.\ $k$,
$$\frac{\hbar^2k}{m_0}=(1+2\alpha\epsilon)\frac{d\epsilon}{dk}
\;\implies\;
v=\frac{1}{\hbar}\frac{d\epsilon}{dk}
=\frac{\hbar k}{m_0(1+2\alpha\epsilon)}.$$
Also $k=\sqrt{\tfrac{2m_0\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}{\hbar^2}}$, so
$$v(\epsilon)
=\frac{\hbar}{m_0(1+2\alpha\epsilon)}\sqrt{\frac{2m_0\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}{\hbar^2}}
=\frac{\sqrt{2m_0\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}}{m_0(1+2\alpha\epsilon)}.$$
3. Acceleration in k-space: 
$$\hbar\frac{dk}{dt}=qE\quad\implies\quad
dt=\frac{\hbar}{qE}\,dk
=\frac{\hbar}{qE}\frac{d\epsilon}{d\epsilon/dk}.$$
Using $d\epsilon/dk=\frac{\hbar^2 k}{m_0(1+2\alpha\epsilon)}$, and changing variables to $\epsilon$:
$$dt=\frac{1}{qE}\frac{m_0(1+2\alpha\epsilon)}{\sqrt{2m_0\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}}\,d\epsilon
=\frac{\sqrt{m_0/2}}{qE}\frac{(1+2\alpha\epsilon)\,d\epsilon}{\sqrt{\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}}.$$
4. Time to reach $\epsilon=\hbar\omega_{iv}$:
$$t_{\rm sat}
=\int_0^{\hbar\omega_{iv}}dt
=\frac{\sqrt{m_0/2}}{qE}
\int_0^{\hbar\omega_{iv}}\frac{(1+2\alpha\epsilon)\,d\epsilon}{\sqrt{\epsilon(1+\alpha\epsilon)}}
=\frac{\sqrt{2m_0\,\hbar\omega_{iv}(1+\alpha\hbar\omega_{iv})}}{qE}.$$
5. Average velocity over one cycle:
$$v_{\rm sat}
=\frac{1}{t_{\rm sat}}\int_0^{t_{\rm sat}}v(t)\,dt
=\frac{1}{t_{\rm sat}}\int_0^{\hbar\omega_{iv}}v(\epsilon)\,\frac{dt}{d\epsilon}\,d\epsilon
=\frac{1}{t_{\rm sat}}\int_0^{\hbar\omega_{iv}}\frac{d\epsilon}{qE}
=\frac{\hbar\omega_{iv}}{qE\,t_{\rm sat}}.$$
6. Substitute $t_{\rm sat}$:
$$v_{\rm sat}
=\frac{\hbar\omega_{iv}}{qE}
\frac{qE}{\sqrt{2m_0\,\hbar\omega_{iv}(1+\alpha\hbar\omega_{iv})}}
=\sqrt{\frac{\hbar\omega_{iv}}{2m_0\bigl(1+\alpha\,\hbar\omega_{iv}\bigr)}}.$$
